---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<BaseLayout title="Learn to Swim — Torquay Leander">

<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="crumb">
      <a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <a href={`${base}/training/`}>Training</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span>Learn to Swim</span>
    </div>
    <h1>Learn to Swim</h1>
    <p>Our Learn to Swim pathway provides a safe and fun introduction to swimming for beginners, building the water confidence and core technique needed to progress into our squads.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="intro">
  <div class="inner intro-inner">
    <p class="label">About Learn to Swim</p>
    <p class="intro-text">Torquay Leander is a competitive swimming club, so we do not teach Learn to Swim within our club sessions. However, we work closely with <strong>Swim Torquay</strong>, whose instructors run Learn to Swim sessions at our pool. Swim Torquay have a team of qualified swimming teachers and coaches, plus a number of poolside assistants, who work with children to provide high-quality tuition and support.</p>
    <p class="intro-text">Learn to Swim sessions teach the important life skill of staying safe in the water. Working through the national swim stages, they give children the skills to become confident swimmers who are able to progress on to our swim squads. Many of our swimmers complete these stages before beginning their journey with us.</p>

    <div class="partner-callout">
      <div class="partner-body">
        <strong>Lessons are run by Swim Torquay</strong>
        <p>To find out more about Learn to Swim lessons, including availability and how to book, please get in touch with Swim Torquay.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="stages">
  <div class="inner">
    <p class="label">Learn to Swim Stages</p>
    <h2>The Stage 1–7 Awards</h2>
    <p class="stages-text">The Learn to Swim Stage 1–7 Awards make up the core national syllabus of learning to swim for primary-school-aged children. They are divided into progressive stages, each with a clear list of outcomes, designed to reward your child as they develop the essential aquatic skills they need to be confident, competent and safe in the water.</p>

    <div class="stage-track">
      <div class="stage-pill"><span>1</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill"><span>2</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill"><span>3</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill"><span>4</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill active"><span>5</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill active"><span>6</span></div>
      <div class="stage-pill active"><span>7</span></div>
    </div>

    <div class="stage-groups">
      <div class="stage-group">
        <span class="sg-range">Stages 1–4</span>
        <h3>Foundations &amp; water confidence</h3>
        <p>Getting comfortable and safe in the water, learning to float, glide and move independently, and developing the building blocks of all four strokes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="stage-group highlight">
        <span class="sg-range">Stages 5–7</span>
        <h3>Refining strokes &amp; squad-ready</h3>
        <p>Refining all four competitive strokes with correct technique, building endurance and water safety. <strong>Swimmers from Stage 5 and above are ready to join a Torquay Leander squad.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="next-step">
      <p>Already swimming at Stage 5 or above? Your swimmer may be ready to join us.</p>
      <a class="next-btn" href={`${base}/about/join/`}>Arrange a free trial →</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--black); padding: 64px 5vw 56px;
    position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .page-hero::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; bottom: -1px; left: 0; right: 0; height: 60px;
    background: #fff; clip-path: polygon(0 100%, 100% 0, 100% 100%);
  }
  .hero-inner { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .crumb { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); font-size: 0.78rem; margin-bottom: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .crumb a { color: var(--red); text-decoration: none; }
  .crumb span { opacity: 0.5; }
  .page-hero h1 { color: #fff; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -1.5px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .page-hero p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65); font-size: 1rem; max-width: 620px; line-height: 1.7; }

  .inner { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .label { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); margin-bottom: 14px; }

  .intro { background: #fff; padding: 72px 5vw 56px; }
  .intro-inner { max-width: 820px; }
  .intro-text { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.85; margin-bottom: 18px; }
  .intro-text strong { color: var(--text); }
  .partner-callout {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 16px;
    background: var(--red-light); border: 1.5px solid #fecaca; border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 22px 24px; margin-top: 14px;
  }
  .partner-body strong { display: block; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .partner-body p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; }

  .stages { background: #f8fafc; padding: 72px 5vw; }
  .stages h2 { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem); font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.5px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .stages-text { color: var(--muted); font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 820px; margin-bottom: 36px; }

  .stage-track { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 40px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .stage-pill {
    width: 52px; height: 52px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: #fff; border: 2px solid var(--border);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    font-weight: 900; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--muted);
    position: relative;
  }
  .stage-pill:not(:last-child)::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 100%; top: 50%; width: 10px; height: 2px; background: var(--border);
  }
  .stage-pill.active { background: var(--red); border-color: var(--red); color: #fff; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(220,38,38,0.3); }

  .stage-groups { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 20px; margin-bottom: 36px; }
  .stage-group { background: #fff; border: 1.5px solid var(--border); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px 26px; }
  .stage-group.highlight { border-color: var(--red); box-shadow: 0 12px 40px rgba(220,38,38,0.08); }
  .sg-range { font-size: 0.72rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 1.5px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--red); }
  .stage-group h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--text); margin: 8px 0 10px; }
  .stage-group p { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }
  .stage-group p strong { color: var(--text); }

  .next-step {
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    background: var(--black); border-radius: 16px; padding: 28px 32px;
  }
  .next-step p { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 0; }
  .next-btn {
    background: var(--red); color: #fff; text-decoration: none;
    padding: 12px 26px; border-radius: 10px; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.92rem;
    white-space: nowrap; transition: transform 0.2s, background 0.2s;
  }
  .next-btn:hover { background: var(--red-dark); transform: translateY(-2px); }

  @media (max-width: 700px) {
    .stage-groups { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .intro, .stages { padding-left: 20px; padding-right: 20px; }
  }
</style>
